  "text": "Disorders with a phenotype showing signi�cant resemblance to PXE and resulting from elastic �ber abnormalities are usually within the group of heritable or acquired skin diseases. Indeed, although elastic �ber fragmentation has been described in eye diseases such as conjunctivochalasis (with �ber fragmentation in the conjunctiva) or in primary open-angle glaucoma (�ber loss and fragmentation in the lamina cribrosa), these entities are clinically completely different from the ophthalmological features in PXE [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . �imilarly, elastic �ber fragmentation has been described in certain tumor types, such as the papillary �broelastoma, but these disorders lie beyond the scope of this paper [CITATION_3] .",
